<div id="review_2596234303" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2596234303" />
    <a title="Kellyn Roth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52072956-kellyn-roth"><img alt="Kellyn Roth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1632622523p2/52072956.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2596234303?book_show_action=true">Nov 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kellyn Roth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kellyn Roth" href="/user/show/52072956-kellyn-roth">Kellyn Roth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=not-for-christians">not-for-christians</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=era-ww2">era-ww2</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=books-for-adults">books-for-adults</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=era-1930s">era-1930s</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=rating-r">rating-r</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=sad-books">sad-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=romance-little-much">romance-little-much</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=own-kindle">own-kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=setting-europe">setting-europe</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52072956-kellyn-roth?shelf=lady-catherine-objects">lady-catherine-objects</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2596234303" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4991933154074464952">Well, that was awful. However, since I DNFed at 21%, perhaps I shouldn&apos;t judge. Still, if the book continues with its horrid writing, lack of editing, dry cutout characters, historical inaccuracies, jumpy timeline, lack of a central character, boring style, and failure to live up to the blurb&apos;s stated plot, it would&apos;ve gotten a 1-star rating if I finished.<br/><br/>If you want to know how the book is written, look no further than the blurb. The novel is written in that exact same style - nothing shown, ev</span>
  <span id="freeText4991933154074464952" style="display:none">Well, that was awful. However, since I DNFed at 21%, perhaps I shouldn't judge. Still, if the book continues with its horrid writing, lack of editing, dry cutout characters, historical inaccuracies, jumpy timeline, lack of a central character, boring style, and failure to live up to the blurb's stated plot, it would've gotten a 1-star rating if I finished.<br /><br />If you want to know how the book is written, look no further than the blurb. The novel is written in that exact same style - nothing shown, everything told. It doesn't just need a good editor; it needs a complete rewrite.<br /><br />I stopped when a "sweet old lesbian couple" popped up. Um, okay? Living publicly in Hitler's Germany? I don't believe it. Furthermore, it's not something I personally support, so it wouldn't do to keep reading.<br /><br />Overall, I can't recommend it to my Christian friends, nor can I honestly recommend it to secular audiences as the writing and historical problems are just too bad.<br /><br /><b>UPDATE:</b><br /><br />It is worth mentioning that shortly after I posted this review, the author contacted me in a common group (on WWII fiction) and publicly lambasted me for posting this review.<br /><br />Of course, she zeroed in on my mention of the lesbian couple - something which, by the way, I was not judging for the fact that they were lesbian but based on the historical inaccuracy {I am a Christian, but would not rate a secular book based on anything that regardless}. I couldn't care less about their relationship; what I care about is a book that accurately represents the historical era. As with many other people who Hitler considered "uglies" for a variety of sick and twisted reasons, homosexual folks were hunted down and persecuted during the reign of the Third Reich. It's very, very wrong, but it's true, and it's not good to hide from the truth.<br /><br />We need more books that show the true horrors of Hitler's Germany.<br /><br />I had had no prior contact with the author, so I found her tagging me in the post/rant somewhat surprising. She was actually fairly respectful at first, although I believe she must have misunderstood my review's point - and although it was inappropriate for her to contact me, of course.<br /><br />However, I was told that if I continued to express my opinions - which countered those of other people in the group who enjoyed the book, felt that negative reviews were unwarranted, or simply insisted that I was a Nazi because I mentioned a lesbian couple in my review as being historically inaccurate - I would be removed from the group.<br /><br />I said, "Okay, do it!" (xD) and was removed. There you go. Freedom of speech. ;) I'm thinking being in a group with those types of people isn't the best place for me anyways. But I wish them well in Christ!<br /><br />(Censorship is also something the Nazis did.) (Funny, isn't it ...)</span>
  <a data-text-id="4991933154074464952" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


