<div id="review_3615593496" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3615593496" />
    <a title="Amanda Lauer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36533224-amanda-lauer"><img alt="Amanda Lauer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1414965732p2/36533224.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3615593496?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amanda Lauer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amanda Lauer" href="/user/show/36533224-amanda-lauer">Amanda Lauer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/56217775-you-are-my-sunshine">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3615593496" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17701840030751682864">I&apos;m very interested in WWII history, so this book was intriguing. The plight of Jews in Europe during the Holocaust was harrowing and Kagan did a good job of bringing those stories to light. The book would have benefitted from tighter copy editing particularly to make the language less modern/American, to keep the timelines straight (was never quite sure what year they were in at the time) and to shorten the book. It was incredibly long. As a writer, I understand not wanting to lose any words th</span>
  <span id="freeText17701840030751682864" style="display:none">I'm very interested in WWII history, so this book was intriguing. The plight of Jews in Europe during the Holocaust was harrowing and Kagan did a good job of bringing those stories to light. The book would have benefitted from tighter copy editing particularly to make the language less modern/American, to keep the timelines straight (was never quite sure what year they were in at the time) and to shorten the book. It was incredibly long. As a writer, I understand not wanting to lose any words that you write after so much research, but audiences in this day and age don't seem to have the patience they did back in the day. That being said, the book has almost 2,000 reviews, so a lot of people are reading it. (What I wouldn't give for 2,000 reviews on any of my books!) This book is part of a series, but can be read as a stand alone, which is what I did since this volume was the one that I had the highest interest in. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17701840030751682864" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


