<div id="review_2106615333" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2106615333" />
    <a title="Tony Parsons" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16535552-tony-parsons"><img alt="Tony Parsons" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1385408225p2/16535552.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2106615333?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tony Parsons" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tony Parsons" href="/user/show/16535552-tony-parsons">Tony Parsons</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2106615333" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer21283127530162624">Germany, Nazi eugenics developed &amp; implemented programs to increase the population of pure Aryan children. <br/>1936, Heinrich Himmler built homes where women of acceptable bloodlines were to be bred with SS officers. <br/><br/>It was called the Institute for the Lebensborn, in Steinhöring, Munich, Germany.<br/>The undesirables, such as: Jews, Gypsies, Jehovah’s Witnesses, homosexuals, the physically or mentally handicapped, were brutally murdered, or gassed/burned alive by Adolph Hitler’s regime.<br/>The journey of sur</span>
  <span id="freeText21283127530162624" style="display:none">Germany, Nazi eugenics developed &amp; implemented programs to increase the population of pure Aryan children. <br />1936, Heinrich Himmler built homes where women of acceptable bloodlines were to be bred with SS officers. <br /><br />It was called the Institute for the Lebensborn, in Steinhöring, Munich, Germany.<br />The undesirables, such as: Jews, Gypsies, Jehovah’s Witnesses, homosexuals, the physically or mentally handicapped, were brutally murdered, or gassed/burned alive by Adolph Hitler’s regime.<br />The journey of survival for pregnant Helga Haswell (wife/mother) abandoned by SS officer Kurt Haswell (husband/father, farmer) begins. <br />10/11/1946, The International Military Tribunal Nuremberg Germany (Palace of Justice) had begun.<br />Zofia Zuckerman (nee Kowalsky, Fruma’s daughter, seamstress, nee Weiss, Jewish), gave her testimony against former Untersturmführer Manfred Blau husband, Treblinka), as Christa Blau (daughter, Manfred’s wife, nee Henkener) sat &amp; watched. <br /><br />Warning: This book is for adults only &amp; contains extreme violent or graphic adult content or profanity &amp;/or sexually explicit scenarios. It may be offensive to some readers. <br /><br />I did not receive any type of compensation for reading &amp; reviewing this book. While I receive free books from publishers &amp; authors, I am under no obligation to write a positive review. Only an honest one. <br /><br />A very awesome book cover, great font &amp; writing style. Wow, a very well written WWII historical fiction book. It was very easy for me to read/follow from start/finish &amp; never a dull moment. There were no grammar/typo errors, nor any repetitive or out of line sequence sentences. Lots of exciting scenarios, with several twists/turns &amp; a large set of unique characters to keep track of. This could also make another great WWII movie, or better yet a mini TV series. A very easy rating of 5 stars. <br /><br />Thank you for the free author; dailyfreebooks; captivatinghistory; Amazon Digital Services LLC.; book <br />Tony Parsons MSW (Washburn)	<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="21283127530162624" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


