    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2870918137" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2870918137" />
    <a title="Joyce" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6137080-joyce"><img alt="Joyce" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1449204493p2/6137080.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2870918137?book_show_action=true">Sep 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joyce" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joyce" href="/user/show/6137080-joyce">Joyce</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6137080-joyce?shelf=foreign-location">foreign-location</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6137080-joyce?shelf=books-read-in-2019">books-read-in-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6137080-joyce?shelf=wwii-era">wwii-era</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6137080-joyce?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6137080-joyce?shelf=holocaust">holocaust</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2870918137" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4655318670773465132">It took me a long time to finish this book because there was so much tragedy in it. I had already read several books set during WWII that involved the plight of the Jews and so put this one aside for a while after I started it. However, once I got back into it, I didn&apos;t want to put it down. <br/><br/>This novel focuses on 2 individuals and their families---Manfred Blau, a German young man and Zofia, a young Jewish woman. Manfred has been a failure at most things until he comes to the attention of Dr. Goeb</span>
  <span id="freeText4655318670773465132" style="display:none">It took me a long time to finish this book because there was so much tragedy in it. I had already read several books set during WWII that involved the plight of the Jews and so put this one aside for a while after I started it. However, once I got back into it, I didn't want to put it down. <br /><br />This novel focuses on 2 individuals and their families---Manfred Blau, a German young man and Zofia, a young Jewish woman. Manfred has been a failure at most things until he comes to the attention of Dr. Goebbels of Nazi party through some work he does for propaganda. He also desires more than anything to win the love of a beautiful German girl Christa, the daughter of a doctor. To achieve that goal, he does everything he can to rise in importance in the Nazi party. <br /><br />As a college age student, Zofia, the young Jewish woman, is seduced by an American teacher and becomes pregnant. Of course, her lover wants nothing to do with her and her mother throws her out. However, she is befriended and given a job by a Jewish woman. This woman also give Zofia and her baby a home.<br /><br />Eventually, the lives of Zofia and Manfred intersect when she is a prisoner at Treblinka and he is the prison's commanding officer. <br /><br />I won't go any further with the summary to avoid spoiling it for other readers. However, it is a book I recommend for those who enjoy reading historical fiction with a holocaust theme. Zofia is a remarkable character who goes through one tragedy after another but emerges strong. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4655318670773465132" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


