    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2099995410" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2099995410" />
    <a title="Mary Little" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37189254-mary-little"><img alt="Mary Little" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1416608906p2/37189254.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2099995410?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary Little" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary Little" href="/user/show/37189254-mary-little">Mary Little</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2099995410" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer270195236524955174">I&apos;ll start with the positives: It was an intriguing story. I did find it hard to put down. Ms. Kagan is a gifted story teller.<br/>The horrifying things that were done to the Jews are something we need to be reminded of as often as possible. The author&apos;s graphic descriptions brought to light the utter abomination of what happened during Nazi Germany&apos;s reign.<br/>Unlike most of the reviewers on here, I was, for the most part, satisfied with the ending. Perhaps it was a bit unrealistic, but I didn&apos;t finish </span>
  <span id="freeText270195236524955174" style="display:none">I'll start with the positives: It was an intriguing story. I did find it hard to put down. Ms. Kagan is a gifted story teller.<br />The horrifying things that were done to the Jews are something we need to be reminded of as often as possible. The author's graphic descriptions brought to light the utter abomination of what happened during Nazi Germany's reign.<br />Unlike most of the reviewers on here, I was, for the most part, satisfied with the ending. Perhaps it was a bit unrealistic, but I didn't finish the book feeling like I was ripped off or that I had wasted my time. <br />It was not necessary to read the first book in order to follow the second.<br /><br />The Negatives: The punctuation was horrendous! Many times I actually found myself laughing at loud at the grammatical errors and misspellings. Some reviewers said they didn't care about the flawed grammar and spelling. Well it matters to me. If you are going to call yourself an author, then learn how to punctuate. It was as if the author had a gun loaded with commas and shot it at the pages. Some of them landed where they weren't needed, others missed the spots they were needed, and some, by coincidence, landed in the right place. <br />Many of the conversations went on way too long. <br />There were many chronological errors as well.<br /><br />As I stated at the beginning, Ms. Kagan is a gifted story teller, but she should consider hiring a ghost writer.</span>
  <a data-text-id="270195236524955174" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


